claim.claim-text:
1. The audio data code conversion and transmission method, comprising:
a step of first audio code conversion and transmission means inputting compressed audio coded data, and outputting all or a part of frames of the input compressed audio coded data;
a step of second to N-th (N is a predetermined integer equal to or larger than 2) audio code conversion and transmission means inputting the compressed audio coded data, decoding all or a part of the input compressed audio coded data, coding the decoded data, and outputting all or a part of frames of the coded data;
a step of means transmitting output of the first to N-th audio code conversion and transmission means to first to M-th (M is a predetermined integer equal to or larger than 1) transmission lines;
a step of selecting a transmission line for receiving the coded data from among first to M-th (M is a predetermined integer equal to 1 or larger) transmission lines; and
a step of receiving the coded data from the selected transmission line, extracting the audio coded data received without a transmission error or a loss, and reconfiguring and outputting the audio coded data based on the extracted coded data.

3. The audio data code conversion and transmission method comprising:
a step of first audio code conversion and transmission means inputting compressed audio coded packet data and outputting all or a part of packets of the input compressed audio coded packet data;
a step of second to N-tb (N is a predetermined integer equal to or larger than 2) audio code conversion and transmission means inputting the compressed audio coded packet data, decoding the input compressed audio coded packet data, coding the decoded packet data, and outputting all or a part of the decoded packet data;
a step of means transmitting output of the first to N-th audio code conversion and transmission means to first to M-th (M is a predetermined integer equal to or larger than 1) transmission lines;
a step of selecting a transmission line for receiving the coded data from among first to M-th (M is a predetermined integer equal to 1 or larger) transmission lines; and
a step of receiving the coded data from the selected transmission line, extracting the audio coded data received without a transmission error or a loss, and reconfiguring and outputting the audio coded data based on the extracted coded data.

